We next modify the collimated white-light beam to produce the necessary condition to de-slant the resonance locus – without altering the cavity itself in any way. The beam is first spatially filtered through a 1-mm-wide vertical slit (to avoid aliasing of multiple resonance orders) and is then diffracted from a reflective grating with 1800 lines/mm Fig. 3b]. The grating produces an angular dispersion of β ≈ 0.09°/nm at λc=550\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
